:"per 1 portions","carbohydrates":"45 g","calories":"2438 kJ \/ 581 kcal"},"usefulItems":"heatproof tea cups or small mugs (Ø 8 cm, height 9 cm), large bowl, refrigerator","hintsAndTricks":["<i>The rich flavours of this lamb stew are enhanced by the overnight marinade with citrus juices, spices and herbs. Steaming rice in cups above the stew allows you to save time and also to present the rice elegantly! The original Caribbean recipe, a classic from the Dominican Republic, is traditionally made with goat meat – try ordering goat at your butcher’s for a slightly more gamey flavour in the stew.<\/i>","For a more traditional, richer flavour, use bone-in meat, increasing the amount of meat to <b>1000 g.<b><br>- <strong>Caribbean Goat Meat Stew:<\/strong> replace lamb meat with <b>1000 g bone-in<b> goat shoulder, cut in <b>5-6 cm pieces.<b> In <b>step 4,<b> cook the stew <b><strong>90 min\/95°C\/\/speed <\/strong><b> before setting the covered Varoma with rice cups on mixing bowl lid – then cook a further <b><strong>30 min\/Varoma\/\/speed .<\/strong><b>"],"basicInfo":["easy","25m","9h 15m","4 portions"]}